# ============================================================================
# _emailengine — zsh completion for **emailengine** —
#                 postalsys/emailengine, the **headless email REST-API
#                 client** that turns any IMAP/SMTP mailbox (Gmail,
#                 Outlook 365, generic IMAPv4, generic Microsoft
#                 Exchange Web Services, Sendgrid relay, etc.) into a
#                 webhook-driven REST + WebSocket service.  Every
#                 incoming message produces a `messageNew` /
#                 `messageDeleted` / `mailboxNew` /
#                 `accountAuthenticationFailure` / `connectError`
#                 webhook (40+ event types); outbound messages go
#                 through `POST /v1/account/<id>/submit` (with full
#                 MIME composition, attachments, threading, BCC,
#                 OAuth2 access-token auto-refresh).  Backed by
#                 Redis-only state (Bull-MQ queues for delivery
#                 retries + DLQ).  Used in production by Postal
#                 Systems' commercial email-routing platform and by
#                 thousands of SaaS apps as their email-ingestion
#                 backplane.  TS-Node=167 CLOSING leg of Axis 112
#                 (WebAuthn / FIDO2 / CTAP2 protocol) at 1/1/1 with
#                 TRIPLE-167 landmark + 105th Axis closed via the
#                 canonical TS/JS WebAuthn SDK **@simplewebauthn/
#                 server** (and its `@simplewebauthn/browser`
#                 client-side counterpart).
